did.abstract: This collection contains correspondence, legal records, and printed matter relating to efforts to determine the fate and resolve the legal status of American servicemen captured or missing in action during the Vietnam War. Includes copies of military records and other government documents released under the Freedom of Information Act.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: The Hoover Institution Archives only allows access to copies of audiovisual items. To listen to sound recordings or to view videos or films during your visit, please contact the Archives at least two working days before your arrival. We will then advise you of the accessibility of the material you wish to see or hear. Please note that not all audiovisual material is immediately accessible.

accruals.head: Accruals
accruals.p: Materials may have been added to the collection since this finding aid was prepared. To determine if this has occurred, find the collection in Stanford University's online catalog at http://searchworks.stanford.edu/. Materials have been added to the collection if the number of boxes listed in the online catalog is larger than the number of boxes listed in this finding aid.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: American lawyer; attorney for families of American servicemen captured or missing in action in the Vietnamese War.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content of Collection
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, legal records, and printed matter relating to efforts to determine the fate and resolve the legal status of American servicemen captured or missing in action during the Vietnam War. Includes copies of military records and other government documents released under the Freedom of Information Act.

did.unittitle: National Human Rights Committee for POW-MIAs,
National League of Families of American Prisoners and Missing in Southeast Asia,

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains memoranda, booklets, transmissions, and other printed matter related to various United States government agencies and branches of the American military, including material on the Freedom of Information Act.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains five manuals titled "Uncorrelated Information Relating to Missing Americans in Southeast Asia" in addition to loose documents.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains four binders in addition to loose documents.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains one binder in addition to loose documents.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains printed summaries of various court cases used for research purposes.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains untitled documents, proposals, worksheets, and other printed matter related to various court cases.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains invoices, receipts, statements, and other printed matter related to the operations of the Law Offices of Walter E. Shjeflo.

did.unittitle: House Select Committee on Missing Persons in Southeast Asia,
National League of Families of American Prisoners and Missing in Southeast Asia,
Presidential Commission on Americans Missing and Unaccounted for in Southeast Asia,

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains statements by Cambodian, Laotian, and Vietnamese refugees sent to families of American POW and MIA soldiers detailing sightings and possible last-known locations of said soldiers.

did.unittitle: National Human Rights Committee for POW-MIAs Newsletter,

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains statements and speeches by William P. Clark, Ann M. Griffiths, T.C. Pinckney, Eugene F. Tighe, and others.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains photographs of missing soldiers, military officials, and meetings between government and military officials.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Contains one bumper sticker that says "Hanoi: Please Release Our POW-MIA."
